title: Only a Dream (from the film "Five Moments") - Ted Ganger
description:
This performance is taken from the award-winning short film "Five Moments," soon to be released in its entirety here on YouTube.

Lyrics and music by Ted Ganger
Magdalena Herfurtner (Madil Hardis), voice
(https://www.youtube.com/c/MadilHardis)
Ted Ganger, piano

#MagdalenaHerfurtner #MadilHardis
#TedGanger

You might also like this song sung (and played) as a "Song of the Week" by Ted Ganger.
https://youtu.be/XP3AvWA6boo

ONLY A DREAM

I dreamed that I lay beside her,                                                                                                                   And we were as we used to be.                                                                                                                    But somehow I couldn't believe it,                                                                                                                 And struggled and tried to get free. 
I cried out: I know I'm dreaming.                                                                                                                 She laughed and kept pulling me in.                                                                                                                I fought my way up to the surface                                                                                                                 And woke, full of what had not been.
 
For that couldn't really happen,                                                                                                                     No matter how things might seem,                                                                                                              So go back to sleep, yes, go back to sleep, just go back to sleep -                                                           It was only a dream.

I dreamed she was going to leave me,                                                                                                        She told me I wasn't the one.                                                                                                                       She smoked on a bench in the moonlight                                                                                                  And spoke what she'd already done.
She thought I should hear it directly,                                                                                                          And now she'd get on with her life.                                                                                                                 I'm still sitting there in the moonlight                                                                                                            And still feel the twist of the knife.

But that never really happened,                                                                                                                      No matter how things might seem,                                                                                                                                  So go back to sleep, yes, go back to sleep, just go back to sleep -                                                                                                It was only a dream.


I dreamed that we once were strangers,                                                                                                          Two souls that had gone astray.                                                                                                                                         We both led the life of the lonely,                                                                                                                                                             And both came from far away.
We knew it would not be easy,                                                                                                                       But felt it was destined to be.                                                                                                                                         So I sent my heart on its journey,                                                                                                                                                 And she shared her secrets with me.

It may be that never happened,                                                                                                                      No matter how things might seem,                                                                                                                                  But go back to sleep, yes, go back to sleep, just go back to sleep -                                                                                            Though it's only a dream.

title: Reduce Back Pain with Dry Cupping and Thread the Needle Stretch
description:
Dawn Morse, founder of Core Elements Training, demonstrates Clinical vacuum Dry Cupping and Thread the Needle stretch. 

Clinical cupping to the back and thread the needle stretch can help to reduce muscular tension whilst increasing blood flow to the area and increasing functional mobility of spine during rotation movement.

title: Maaf Karde by Mustafa Zahid | New Hamd Release | Playback Records
description:
Welcome to the official YouTube channel of Playback Records. We are deeply honored and privileged to present to you a soul-stirring hamd "Maaf Krde" by the renowned artist Mustafa Zahid.

Through this beautiful hamd, Mustafa Zahid offers a heartfelt prayer seeking forgiveness and expressing sincere remorse to the Almighty. The poignant lyrics and the mesmerizing melody of this hamd are sure to touch your heart and soul, leaving you with a feeling of serenity and spiritual awakening.

The raw emotion and sheer passion in Mustafa Zahid's voice will leave you spellbound and make you feel the depth of the message conveyed through this hamd. We are proud to bring you this new hamd release that is not just music, but a journey of spiritual reflection and devotion.

We invite you to join us on this beautiful journey and experience the beauty of Mustafa Zahid's incredible talent and devotion to the Almighty. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more heart-touching hamd videos and recitations. Thank you for your support!

title: Double Decker Sandwich
description:
Enjoy Mouth Watering Young's Double Decker Sandwich!

Ingredients for Chicken Patty (For three persons)

Chicken mince: 250gm
Garlic ginger paste: 2 Tablespoons
Green coriander (Finely chopped): 2 Tablespoons 
Green chili (Finely chopped): 2
Breadcrumbs: Half cup
Salt: As per taste
Cooking Oil: Half cup

Preparation for Chicken Patty 
Mix all the above ingredients well and make thin square patties and fry them in cooking oil.

Ingredients for Sandwich:
Young's Mayonnaise: 1 Cup
Bread slices (Make toast): 9
Cucumber (Cut into slices) 1
Tomato (Cut into slices): 2
Lettuce leaves: 6 
Toothpicks: 12

Preparation for Sandwich
Place a lettuce leave on a slice of bread with Young's Mayonnaise and place the chicken patty on it. Then place four tomato slices on the chicken patty. Now add another bread slice with Young's Mayonnaise on it and put another lettuce leaf and add another chicken patty and four cucumber slices over tomato slices and cover it with the third bread slice with Young's Mayonnaise. Now cut the sandwich into two pieces with the help of a toothpick. Young's Double Decker Sandwich is ready€î

description:
Young's Chop Suey!! A must delicacy in Iftar

Ingredients for Noodles (For 5 persons)
Spaghetti: Half packet
Salt: As per taste
Water: Boiled 1 liter 
Cooking oil: As required

Preparation for Noodles
Boil water in a pan, add salt and spaghetti, and cook for 5 minutes. When the spaghetti boils, strain it. Heat oil in a pan and fry the spaghetti until golden brown. (The spaghetti will form a bunch)

Ingredients for Young's Mayo Chicken Sauce

Young's Mayonnaise: 1.5 Cup
Chicken fillet: 250gm (Cut thinly into long pieces)
Soy sauce: 2 Tablespoons
Carrot: 1 medium size
Capsicum: 1
Green onion (Chop finely) 1 Tablespoon
Garlic ginger paste: 1 Tablespoon
Red pepper (Powdered) 1 Teaspoon
Tomato: 2
Onion: 1
Green coriander: 1 Tablespoon
Salt: As per taste
Cooking oil: 3 Tablespoons

Preparation for Young's Mayo Chicken Sauce
Add garlic, ginger paste, salt, red pepper, and soy sauce to the chicken fillet and marinate for 15 minutes. Heat oil in a pan and fry the chicken, then add all the vegetables and saute well, then add water and Young's mayonnaise. The delicious Young's Mayo Chicken Sauce is ready

Chop Suey Serving:
Layer the fried noodles in the dish and pour Young's Mayo Chicken Sauce over it, then sprinkle coriander, and green onions on top. The delicious Young's Chop Suey is ready€î

title: Humpbacks and Heartful Breathing for Interdependence (with BSL) | Sulaiman Khan | TEDxLadbrokeGrove
description:
Sulaiman challenges the idea that an individual‚Äôs worth and value are defined by their health, productivity, or earning potential. Gain a whale of actionable insights for the post-pandemic future of work through the lens of Disabled creativity. With thanks to Love Language for providing BSL interpretation. Sulaiman is an independent consultant, speaker, and writer on Disability, Creativity, and Equitability.
Sulaiman [he/him/Disabled] loves to create relationships, stories, and magic. He is the award-winning Founder and Chief Purpose Officer of ThisAbility Limited, a disability-led equity business. ThisAbility helps socially conscious organisations focused on sustainability, technology, or design to increase revenues by engaging the estimated $8 Trillion disabled market.

Sulaiman is also the Co-Founder at Cripjoy, a transnational, majority-BIPOC community of practice reworlding mental health through an intersectional, anti-ableist, and anti-sanist lens.

With over 35-years‚Äô lived-experience of disability and over 10-years‚Äô experience in the creative industries, he works tirelessly to ignite, invest in, and amplify disabled creativity across the world for a Just tomorrow for disabled people. YummY And Delicious Biryani Recipe | Chicken Masala Biryani By Continental Food
description:
Chicken Masala Biryani | Super Easy Biryani Recipe By Continental Food (Special For beginners)
Biryani is prepared using fragrant rice, aromatic spices, and chicken. It is prepared in many ways and Continental Food presents to you the delicious and the easiest one a Ramzan Special Biryani. So watch and learn how to make Chicken Biryani only on Continental Food

Ingredients for Chicken Biryani: 
 1.1 cup cooking oil
 2. 2 chopped onion
 3. brown cardamon
 4. star anise
 5. cinnamon stick
 6. javentri whole
 7. 1 tbsp cumin seeds
 8. 2 tbsp ginger & garlic paste
 9. chicken 1 kg
10. 1 tbsp salt
11. 1 tsp turmeric powder
12. 1 tbsp red chilli powder
13. 1tbsp coriander powder
14. 1 tbsp ground spice powder
15. 2 tbsp biryani masala
16. 2 chopped tomato
17. 1 cup yogurt
18. green chilli & fresh coriander
19. 3 cup boiled rice 
20. yellow food colour 2 pinch mix with water
for garnish boiled egg ( optional )
lemon/green chilli/fresh coriander!!

                 
So, all of your following queries are resolved here:-

1. Simple Chicken Biryani for Beginners 
2. How To Make Chicken Biryani 
3. Easy Chicken Biryani Recipe
4. Chicken Biryani with Biryani Masala 
5. Super Easy Chicken Biryani for Bachelors 

Frequently Asked Questions:

1. What does biryani taste like?
Image result for biryani
Biryani is known for its aroma and flavor. Fresh herbs, saffron, and basmati rice give it a sweet-floral aroma that hits the nose before you taste it. Whole garam masala, fried onions, and marinated meat provide warmth and subtle heat to the dish. Overall, it tastes like a savory, spiced rice pilaf.

2. What is in biryani?
The Components. What is biryani made of? Any type of biryani consists of four main components: rice, meat, marinade, and spices.     

3.Is biryani a curry?
WHAT IS BIRYANI, AND WHY DO I LOVE IT SO MUCH? Essentially, it's your favourite chicken curry (or vegetable or other protein of choice) buried under a mound of delicately spiced fluffy rice, all made in one pot.

4. What is biryani without meat called?
‚ÄúVeg biryani is as much a biryani as a non-veg one if it is made by layering and cooking on dum. The vegetables and the spices create a m√©lange of flavours and aroma which tickle your taste buds as much as a biryani with meat would do.

5.Why do people love biryani so much?
Biryani communicates a sense of home that reminds people of belonging. Furthermore, it traces them back to their old memories of home, family, and loved ones. So, in essence, Biryani is not just any other dish, it is a desi dish.

description:
The Best Of Urdu Motivational Poetry: "peyar Zindagi Hai" Love is life, but only for those who understand it, practice it, and share it. Those who share love always receive love. Love is a priceless treasure and a magical feeling that speaks to the heart. 
In this video, you will see different forms of love and learn about its importance. Love brings happiness, radiance, and a magnetic force. It even turns enemies into friends. Understanding love brings us closer to God because He loves His people deeply.

"I am Ruby Khan, and I love to write, my poetry reflects all the different parts of life, #love, #pain, #happiness, #meeting people, saying goodbye, waiting, and reuniting.

title: ISTANBUL | Center of the world | 4k üáπüá∑
description:
Istanbul is a major city in Turkey that straddles Europe and Asia across the Bosphorus Strait. Its Old City reflects cultural influences of the many empires that once ruled here. In the Sultanahmet district, the open-air, Roman-era Hippodrome was for centuries the site of chariot races, and Egyptian obelisks also remain. The iconic Byzantine Hagia Sophia features a soaring 6th-century dome and rare Christian mosaics.

Once Constantinople, this had always been the center of the world and the most important stronghold in the Roman Empire for almost 10 centuries. Followed by the Ottoman Empire. The city holds a blend of historical and cultural heritage that stretches far beyond around the globe. Here is my take  on some of the things you can visit and do in the city of Istanbul. Hope you enjoy!

title: Lemon Polenta Cake | Wholesome Bellies By Fi
description:
Welcome to Wholesome Bellies By Fi! In this video, we're sharing a delicious recipe for Lemon Polenta Cake that's sure to impress. 

This Lemon Polenta Cake is a delightful treat for afternoon tea or any occasion. Its lightness and subtle sweetness make it a perfect choice when you're craving a refreshing dessert. With the option to freeze slices and the ability to last up to a week in the fridge, it's a convenient and delicious option to enjoy at your own pace.

This cake is incredibly light and not very sweet! Which some days is exactly what I‚Äôm looking for. And if you love a strong lemon flavour, we‚Äôve added lemon essential oils (food grade) to our recipe. This special edition gives the cake an extra punch. Infusing the entire cake with an intense burst of tangy citrus goodness. Each bite becomes a flavor explosion, leaving a zesty and refreshing sensation that lingers on the taste buds. The use of lemon essential oils adds depth and complexity to the overall taste experience, making this cake a true standout for lemon enthusiasts.


**INGREDIENTS

‚óè 2 flax eggs (1 flax egg is 1 tablespoon flax meal and 3 tablespoons water)
‚óè 1/2 cup coconut milk
‚óè ¬Ω cup maple syrup 
‚óè ¬Ω cup coconut sugar 
‚óè ¬Ω cup lemon juice
‚óè Zest from two lemons 
‚óè 1 cup coconut plain yogurt
‚óè ¬Ω cup olive oil 9
‚óè 1 1/4 cup polenta 
‚óè 1 ¬Ω cups almond meal 
‚óè ¬Ω cup gluten plain flour
‚óè 1 1/2 teaspoons baking powder
‚óè 1 teaspoon bicarb soda
‚óè 5 drops of lemon DoTerra food-grade essential oils



**METHOD

Make the flax egg by mixing six tablespoons of water with 2 tablespoons of flax meal.  Let sit for two minutes.
In a large bowl mix in coconut milk, maple syrup, coconut sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind, yogurt, olive oil, and then the rested flax eggs.
In a second bowl mix in the polenta, almond meal, flour and baking powder, and bicarb soda.
Then add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture and mix to form a cake batter.
Place into a greased 25cm round spring form tin and back for 40 minutes at 180 degrees.


***PREP TIME
Around 20 minutes 

***COOK TIME
Around 40 minutes

It is just 10 minutes voice note. In this series, I am reciting in Urdu Sahih Bukrai Hadiths in sequence without any explanation.
·π¢a·∏•ƒ´·∏• al-BukhƒÅrƒ´ (Arabic: ÿµÿ≠Ÿäÿ≠ ÿßŸÑÿ®ÿÆÿßÿ±Ÿä‚Äé) is one of the Kutub al-Sittah (six major hadith collections) of Sunni Islam. Whereas, out of all these six major books, the collection of prophetic traditions, or hadith for Sahih al-Bukhari, was performed by the Muslim scholar Muhammad al-Bukhari. It was completed around 846 AD / 232 AH. Sunni Muslims view this as one of the two most trusted collections of hadith along with Sahih Muslim.[1][2] The Arabic word sahih translates as authentic or correct.[3] Sahih al-Bukhari, together with Sahih Muslim is known as Sahihayn.

BUILDING RELATIONS SINCE 12 YEARS
Asparagus Hospitality Administration Services (AHAS)
Asparagus Hospitality started its journey from 2010 with Event and Wedding Planning Services, with inhouse Food Catering and Decoration Unit , under the Brand name Asparagus Catering Unit and Asparagus Event and Wedding Decors respectively  which helped them to maintain the same quality and pocket friendly budget for their clients.

Founder Pritam Dutta , Alumni IHM Taratala (Kolkata) spread Asparagus‚Äôs services to Destination Weddings , Promoting Bengal‚Äôs Off beat destinations for Exotic Events and Weddings , and expanded its services to North East Part of India also.

A destination wedding is any wedding in which the engaged couples and a majority of their guests travel to attend the wedding ceremony.
Destination weddings give the couple the opportunity to choose a site that has a special meaning for them, such as a favorite country or mountain view or beach or they might simply choose a beautiful location they'd like to spend time in with their close friends and families. 

ASPARAGUS CATERING UNIT 
a food catering house which offers conceptual ways to bring the platter from the kitchen to its guests ensuring the basic need for anyone ‚Äì SATISFACTION. 

Its not only food , but along with the quality of food , its way of service , hygiene and new measures of presentation and art of cooking is taken care over here .  

We are the most budget friendly ‚ÄúCatering Unit in Kolkata‚Äù who customizes menus in different budget segments according to guest need. 
Its better to do any job when you have the perfect combination of both technical and practical exposure which is also the reason of our success since years.

We have a selective range of menus from different cuisines including both vegetarian and non-vegetarian platters. We are one of the very few ‚ÄúCatering Service Provider‚Äù who serve their guests with international palettes by professional management team. Our service varies from Platter to plate, American service and Buffet services.

Awarded at BENGAL - AN INSPIRATIONAL LEADERSHIP AWARDS 2018.
Bengal - An Inspirational Leaders Award 2018 is a felicitation program is to recognize , respect , honour and felicitate the Eminent personalities , from different fields of life and profession , for their outstanding contribution to the respective industry and this city / state & also to the society through several acts of humanity and mankind which took place in Kolkata at Kalakunj , Kalamandir.

We have achieved much fame by getting selected in 
‚ÄúAHARE BANGLA -2016, 2017 , 2018 , 2019‚Äù 
a food festival organized by the West Bengal government  We were honored by getting the biggest stall in the food carnival amongst private food service provider and a separate stalls for our International exotic delicacies and theme food in their theme food pavilion. More than Lacs of food lovers were served each day and its only because of our team effort we succeeded. You can find our menus of the food festival at a later stage.
Won The Best Menu Award for one of our exotic collections in the year 2018.

‚ÄúBENGAL FISH FEST, 2017 , 2018 , 2019 , 2020 ‚Äù 
organized by Department of Fisheries ,  Govt. of West Bengal  and Indian Chamber of Commerce 
was another food festival dedicated to fish lovers where we have acquired unpredictable success that has helped us aim for the stars. 
Lots of people enjoyed our delicious, mouth- watering dishes and we received positive feedback from every visitor. We learnt that how much important good food was as it helped a person remember the brand. This is key of success by which we want to uplift our company.

Asparagus Hospitality from the year 2014 started acquiring few banquets in Kolkata , and provided end to end Event Management Solutions under budget and premium packages. We also have business models for other banquet / venue owners under which they can earn a steady income with less engagement.

Asparagus Started ALDP ( Asparagus Learning and Development Program) from the year 2018 and presently train candidates interested in hospitality . Later the Company absorbs them as partimers or full timers in their projects only.

Asparagus Entrepreneurship Scheme (AES) , assists new upcoming entrepreneurs who wants to build their careers or enter into hospitality industry with all necessary guidance from licensing , manpower , operations and sales.

Welcome to this ProfileTree Wix tutorial.
In this video, we will show you how to add and customise forms on your Wix website. 
This is the perfect Wix tutorial for beginners and feel free to pause as you move through the video to help you follow along.

Custom forms are beneficial on websites for several reasons:

Collecting user information: Custom forms allow websites to collect specific user information that can be used for various purposes, such as lead generation, customer feedback, and online orders. By gathering this information, businesses can better understand their customers and tailor their services to meet their needs.

Improved user experience: Custom forms provide a more streamlined and intuitive user experience compared to traditional forms. They can be designed to match the website's branding and be optimized for mobile devices, making it easier for users to fill out and submit information.

Data accuracy: Custom forms can be designed to ensure data accuracy, reducing errors and eliminating the need for manual data entry. This can save businesses time and improve the accuracy of their data, leading to better decision-making.

Security: Custom forms can be designed with security in mind, ensuring that sensitive user information is protected from unauthorized access. This can help businesses comply with data protection laws and regulations.

Automation: Custom forms can be integrated with automation tools, such as email marketing and customer relationship management (CRM) software. This integration can streamline business processes, automate follow-up communications, and improve customer engagement.

Customization: Custom forms can be customized to meet specific business requirements, such as conditional logic, multi-step forms, and custom input fields. This customization can help businesses gather the exact information they need from their customers.

In summary, custom forms are beneficial on websites because they allow businesses to collect user information, improve user experience, ensure data accuracy, provide security, automate processes, and customize forms to meet specific business requirements. These benefits can lead to better customer engagement, increased efficiency, and improved decision-making for businesses.

title: Exploring Shipwrecks in the Cayman Islands with an Underwater Submarine
description:
Exploring Shipwrecks in the Cayman Islands with an Underwater Submarine

The video showcases a trip to Cayman Island where the viewers are taken on a submarine tour to explore shipwrecks in the sea. The tour guide provides information about the history of the shipwrecks, including their size, origin, and how they sunk. The viewers also get to see different species of fishes and birds. The video ends with the tour guide showcasing the local cuisine and trying out the island's traditional dish, snapper modulus. Overall, the video provides an informative and enjoyable experience of the Cayman Island tour.

description:
If there's ever been a time when we needed a boost in RESILIENCY, it's now.

Let's face it‚Äîdivorce, health issues, financial crises, and other major challenges can really knock us down, both emotionally and physically. We can't avoid the punches, setbacks, and unexpected losses that leave us feeling devastated for what seems like forever.

But here's the smart move: learn how to manage these curveballs with an OPTIMAL RESILIENCE MINDSET.

This week, I have the privilege of speaking with the incredible resilience expert, DR. TARYN MARIE. Dr. Marie discovered that resilience was the key to healing and minimizing ongoing trauma. Her work as the founder of the RESILIENCE LEADERSHIP INSTITUTE and author of the NY TIMES best-selling book, THE FIVE PRACTICES OF HIGHLY RESILIENT PEOPLE, has made her a sought-after keynote speaker and a favorite among podcast listeners.

Get ready to soak up some wisdom as we explore:

Unveiling the true essence of resiliency

How CHALLENGE, CHANGE, and COMPLEXITY are intertwined with resilience

Debunking the 5 Myths of Resilient People

The power of creating a REVERSE BUCKET LIST

Navigating the tricky terrain of vulnerability and overcoming SHAME BIAS

Harnessing the strength of PRODUCTIVE PERSEVERANCE

A deep dive into the world of GRIT

Uncovering the habits and characteristics of resilient individuals

Rituals that cultivate a RESILIENT LIFE

But that's not all‚Äîwe also delve into crucial conversations about equipping parents with the tools to raise resilient children and reflecting on the messages our older selves should have imparted to our younger selves.

Here's the bottom line: When we embrace vulnerability, thoughtfulness, and perseverance, we equip ourselves with the essential tools to lead resilient lives. Get ready to transform your mindset and unleash your resilience!
